devdoc.details: Implements role-based access control with hierarchical ranks.

AccessDenied(address,uint8).details: Error thrown when an account lacks the required rank.

params.account: The address of the account attempting the operation.
params.requiredRank: The rank required for the operation.

InvalidOperation(string).details: Error thrown when an invalid operation is attempted.

params.reason: The reason why the operation is invalid.

RankAssigned(address,uint8).details: Emitted when a rank is assigned to an account.

params.account: The address of the account being assigned a rank.
params.rank: The rank assigned to the account.

RankDowngraded(address,uint8).details: Emitted when an account's rank is downgraded.

params.account: The address of the account being downgraded.
params.newRank: The new rank assigned to the account.

RankRevoked(address).details: Emitted when a rank is revoked from an account.

params.account: The address of the account whose rank is revoked.

RankUpgraded(address,uint8).details: Emitted when an account's rank is upgraded.

params.account: The address of the account being upgraded.
params.newRank: The new rank assigned to the account.

assignRank(address,uint8).details: Can only be called by accounts with CONSUL rank or higher.

params.account: The address to assign the rank to.

constructor.details: Constructor that assigns the deployer the highest rank (PREATORMAXIMUS).

downgradeRank(address).details: Can only be called by accounts with CONSUL rank or higher.

params.account: The address to downgrade the rank for.

returns._0: Rank The rank of the account.

params.account: The address of the account to check.

returns._0: bool True if the account has the required rank or higher, false otherwise.

revokeRank(address).details: Can only be called by accounts with SENATOR rank or higher.

params.account: The address to revoke the rank from.

upgradeRank(address).details: Can only be called by accounts with CONSUL rank or higher.

params.account: The address to upgrade the rank for.
